Monolith (no auth)

This is the standard single-repository monolith layout generated when `projectType` is `monolith` and auth is disabled.

my-monolith-app/
  src/
    config/
    middlewares/
    modules/
      v1/
        health/
    utils/
    app.ts (or app.js)
    routes.ts (or routes.js)
    server.ts (or server.js)
  package.json
  README.md
  .env.example

Notes for monolith:
- If you enable auth the monolith will include `src/modules/v1/auth/` and `src/models/` for user models.
- The monolith ships with a single `package.json` and top-level tooling (ESLint, Prettier, Husky) configured at the repository root.

Common notes

- `shared/config/` contains environment mapping and shared configuration used by services or the monolith.
- `shared/utils/` contains logger and helper utilities.
- The root `README.md` is generated and updated to reflect created services when you add new services in microservice mode.

